title: Big Cat Diary [Season 1] - 6 Episodes
description:
Filmed in Masai Mara, Africa, big cats such as lions, leopards and cheetahs are shown in their natural habitat. The presenters offer commentary and focus on big cats with cubs and lion prides.




Plots:
----------
Episode 1:

Half-Tail has a job on hand raising 6-7 month cub Shadow to adulthood having only raised one cub previously. Will Shadow make it to adulthood
The Marsh Pride of Lions are the lion stars with 4 adult males, 7 adult females and 17 cubs. Will the pride stay intact and raise all the cubs
Two families of cheetahs including Fundi and Kidogo the cheetahs and their cubs have more of a struggle on survival with leopards, lions and hyenas that can and will kill cheetahs cubs and adults will any cats survive?


Episode 2:

Amber the cheetah's cubs seem ready to leave their mother as they succeed in catching an adult impala. But then Simon discovers that they are not as advanced as they seem. First, they kill a topi calf but, in doing so, attract the anger of the adults, then they take on a troop of baboons and are forced to beat a hurried retreat.
